    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-12-26T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-12-26T10:00:00-05:00" n="926"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d926">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/26722: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-12-26T17:00:00+02:00"
                            >December 26, 1942—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 27—5:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1354. Embassy Naval Attaché has drawn my attention to four Axis barges which
                    passed through Bosphorus headed for Aegean on December 23. He states that
                    although these barges give every appearance of being commercial vessels they are
                    obviously intended for military purposes and that he is informed that a
                    considerable <pb facs="0823" n="811" xml:id="pg_811"/> additional number have
                    been assembled along Black Sea coast and a number during past year.</p>
                <p>British Chargé with whom I discussed matter this morning states that under
                    instructions from London he is protesting to Foreign Office today. I told him
                    that unless he received satisfactory assurances from Foreign Office on subject I
                    would protest at once against passage of any more of these barges.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
